Norris G. STOREY, Appellant, v. ACCIDENT & CASUALTY INSURANCE COMPANY OF WINTERTHUR, SWITZERLAND, Appellee. No. 9997. Circuit Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. March 26, 1942. Joseph A. Loret, of Baton Rouge, La., for appellant. John C. Hollingsworth, of New Orleans, La., for appellee.

Before HUTCHESON, HOLMES, and McCORD, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon the authority of Hunteman v. New Orleans Public Service, 5 Cir., 119 F.2d 465, the appeal is dismissed.
